"761","<TYPE>INTERNAL CONTROL RPT"
"762","<SEQUENCE>2"
"763","<FILENAME>Hussman_N-CEN_Opinion.htm"
"764","<TEXT>"
"765","<HTML>"
"766","<HEAD>"
"767","     <TITLE></TITLE>"
"768","</HEAD>"
"769","<BODY STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif>"
"770","<P STYLE=margin: 0></P>"
"771","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: center><B>Report of Independent Registered Public Accounting"
"772","Firm</B></P>"
"773","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0>&nbsp;</P>"
"774","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0>To the Shareholders and Board of Trustees of</P>"
"775","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0>Hussman Investment Trust</P>"
"776","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0>&nbsp;</P>"
"777","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0>In planning and performing our audit of the financial statements"
"778","of Hussman Investment Trust (the Funds) as of and for the year ended June 30, 2018, in accordance with the standards of the Public"
"779","Company Accounting Oversight Board (United States), we considered the Funds&rsquo; internal control over financial reporting, including"
"780","controls over safeguarding securities, as a basis for designing our auditing procedures for the purpose of expressing our opinion"
"781","on the financial statements and to comply with the requirements of Form N-CEN, but not for the purpose of expressing an opinion"
"782","on the effectiveness of the Funds&rsquo; internal control over financial reporting. Accordingly, we express no such opinion.</P>"
"783","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0>&nbsp;</P>"
"784","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0>The management of the Funds is responsible for establishing and"
"785","maintaining effective internal control over financial reporting. In fulfilling this responsibility, estimates and judgments by"
"786","management are required to assess the expected benefits and related costs of controls. A fund&rsquo;s internal control over financial"
"787","reporting is a process designed to provide reasonable assurance regarding the reliability of financial reporting and the preparation"
"788","of financial statements for external purposes in accordance with generally accepted accounting principles. A fund&rsquo;s internal"
"789","control over financial reporting includes those policies and procedures that (1) pertain to the maintenance of records that, in"
"790","reasonable detail, accurately and fairly reflect the transactions and dispositions of the assets of the fund; (2) provide reasonable"
"791","assurance that transactions are recorded as necessary to permit preparation of financial statements in accordance with generally"
"792","accepted accounting principles, and that receipts and expenditures of the fund are being made only in accordance with authorizations"
"793","of management and directors of the fund; and (3) provide reasonable assurance regarding prevention or timely detection of unauthorized"
"794","acquisition, use or disposition of a funds&rsquo; assets that could have a material effect on the financial statements.</P>"
"795","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0>&nbsp;</P>"
"796","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0>Because of its inherent limitations, internal control over financial"
"797","reporting may not prevent or detect misstatements. Also, projections of any evaluation of effectiveness to future periods are subject"
"798","to the risk that controls may become inadequate because of changes in conditions, or that the degree of compliance with the policies"
"799","or procedures may deteriorate.</P>"
"800","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0>&nbsp;</P>"
"801","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0>A deficiency in internal control over financial reporting exists"
"802","when the design or operation of a control does not allow management or employees, in the normal course of performing their assigned"
"803","functions, to prevent or detect misstatements on a timely basis. A material weakness is a deficiency, or a combination of deficiencies,"
"804","in internal control over financial reporting, such that there is a reasonable possibility that a material misstatement of the funds&rsquo;"
"805","annual or interim financial statements will not be prevented or detected on a timely basis.</P>"
"806","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0>&nbsp;</P>"
"807","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0>Our consideration of the Funds&rsquo; internal control over financial"
"808","reporting was for the limited purpose described in the first paragraph and would not necessarily disclose all deficiencies in internal"
"809","control that might be material weaknesses under standards established by the Public Company Accounting Oversight Board (United"
"810","States). However, we noted no deficiencies in the Funds&rsquo; internal control over financial reporting and its operation, including"
"811","controls over safeguarding securities, that we consider to be a material weakness as defined above as of June 30, 2018.</P>"
"812","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0>&nbsp;</P>"
"813","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0>This report is intended solely for the information and use of management"
"814","and the Board of Trustees of the Hussman Investment Trust and the Securities and Exchange Commission and is not intended to be"
"815","and should not be used by anyone other than these specified parties.</P>"
"816","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0>&nbsp;</P>"
"817","<TABLE CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=0 STYLE=width: 100%; font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; border-collapse: collapse>"
