"839","<BODY STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif>"
"840","<P STYLE=margin: 0></P>"
"841","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: center><B>TRIBUNE LITIGATION DISCLOSURE</B><BR>"
"842","<B>(For Annual Report &ndash; June 30, 2018)</B></P>"
"843","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: center><B>&nbsp;</B></P>"
"844","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0><B>Item G.1.a.i. Legal Proceedings</B></P>"
"845","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0><B>&nbsp;</B></P>"
"846","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.5in>Several lawsuits have been"
"847","filed relating to Hussman Strategic Growth Fund&rsquo;s investment in Tribune Company common stock in connection with Tribune Company&rsquo;s"
"848","Chapter 11 bankruptcy. The lawsuits stem from a leveraged buyout by which Tribune Company converted to a privately-held company"
"849","in 2007. The Trust, Hussman Strategic Growth Fund and the Adviser (the &quot;Hussman Entities&quot;) were named as defendants and"
"850","putative members of the proposed defendant class of shareholders in an adversary proceeding brought by The Official Committee of"
"851","Unsecured Creditors of Tribune Company in the U.S. Bankruptcy Court for the District of Delaware in 2010. That action was subsequently"
"852","transferred to the U.S. District Court for the Southern District of New York by order of the Judicial Panel on Multidistrict Litigation,"
"853","and Marc S. Kirschner, the Litigation Trustee for the Tribune Litigation Trust, became successor plaintiff to the Creditors Committee"
"854","on December 31, 2012, the effective date of Tribune Company&rsquo;s plan of reorganization. The Trust and Hussman Strategic Growth"
"855","Fund were also named as defendants in a lawsuit filed by the indenture trustees of certain noteholders of Tribune Company in the"
"856","U.S. District Court for the Southern District of Ohio in 2011. Hussman Strategic Growth Fund and the Adviser were named as defendants"
"857","in a similar action in the U.S. District Court for the District of Maryland in 2011. Both of those actions have been transferred"
"858","to the U.S. District Court for the Southern District of New York for coordinated proceedings with many other similar lawsuits brought"
"859","by individual creditors against former Tribune Company shareholders and the action currently prosecuted by the Tribune Litigation"
"860","Trustee. The Trust, Hussman Strategic Growth Fund and the Adviser may also be putative defendant class members in some of these"
"861","actions. The plaintiffs in all these lawsuits seek to recover amounts paid to shareholders of Tribune Company in connection with"
"862","the leveraged buyout, plus interest and attorneys&rsquo; fees and expenses.</P>"
"863","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.5in>&nbsp;</P>"
"864","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.5in>An omnibus motion to dismiss"
"865","the actions filed by the individual creditors (the &quot;Individual Creditor Actions&quot;), but not the action prosecuted by the"
"866","Litigation Trustee for the Tribune Litigation Trust (the &quot;Litigation Trustee Action&quot;), was filed in November 2012. On"
"867","September 23, 2013, the U.S. District Court Judge issued a decision and order dismissing the Individual Creditor Actions in full."
"868","The plaintiffs in those actions appealed that decision to the U.S. Court of Appeals for the Second Circuit and certain shareholder"
"869","defendants, including each of the Hussman Entities, cross-appealed. The Second Circuit heard oral argument on November 5, 2014"
"870","and issued a unanimous decision affirming the District Court&rsquo;s decision on March 29, 2016. A petition of the individual creditors"
"871","for rehearing or rehearing <I>en banc</I> was denied by the Second Circuit on July 22, 2016. The individual creditors filed a petition"
"872","for a writ of certiorari in the United States Supreme Court on September 9, 2016, seeking Supreme Court review of the Second Circuit"
"873","decision.</P>"
"874","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.5in>&nbsp;</P>"
"875","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.5in>On August 2, 2013, with"
"876","the District Court&rsquo;s permission, the Litigation Trustee filed an amended complaint in the Litigation Trustee Action that"
"877","named Hussman Strategic Growth Fund as one of the class representatives for the putative class of shareholder defendants. The Court"
"878","issued a protocol regarding a global motion to dismiss that was filed on behalf of all shareholder defendants on April 24, 2014"
"879","and the District Court issued an opinion and order granting the motion to dismiss on January 6, 2017. The Litigation Trustee sought"
"880","leave to appeal the District Court&rsquo;s order, and the District Court has indicated that it will certify an interlocutory appeal"
"881","after it resolves all other pending motions to dismiss.</P>"
"882","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.5in>&nbsp;</P>"
"883","<!-- Field: Page; Sequence: 1 -->"
"884","    <DIV STYLE=margin-bottom: 6pt><P STYLE=margin-top: 0pt; text-align: center; margin-bottom: 0pt; font: 9pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif><!-- Field: Sequence; Type: Arabic; Name: PageNo; Options: Hidden -->&nbsp;<!-- Field: /Sequence -->&nbsp;</P></DIV>"
"885","    <DIV STYLE=page-break-before: always; margin-top: 6pt><P STYLE=margin: 0pt>&nbsp;</P></DIV>"
"886","    <!-- Field: /Page -->"
"887","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify></P> <P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.5in></P>"
"888","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.5in>The Litigation Trustee"
"889","is seeking to amend his complaint in the Litigation Trustee Action to add a claim for constructive fraudulent conveyance against"
"890","the shareholder defendants based on the Supreme Court&rsquo;s decision in <I>Merit Management Group, LP v. FTI Consulting, Inc.</I>,"
"891","No. 16-784 (U.S.) (&ldquo;<I>Merit Management</I>&rdquo;). In addition, the Litigation Trustee has requested that the District"
"892","Court defer certification of an interlocutory appeal from the Court's dismissal of the Litigation Trustee&rsquo;s intentional"
"893","fraudulent conveyance claim.</P>"
"894","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.5in>&nbsp;</P>"
"895","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.5in>Although the District Court"
"896","denied the Litigation Trustee&rsquo;s motion to amend its complaint on August 24, 2017, the Litigation Trustee renewed the motion"
"897","to amend on March 8, 2018, based on the Supreme Court's decision in <I>Merit Management</I>. That motion has been stayed by the"
"898","District Court pending action by the Second Circuit in the Individual Creditor Actions.</P>"
"899","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify>&nbsp;</P>"
"900","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.5in>On April 10, 2018, the"
"901","plaintiffs in the Individual Creditor Actions filed a motion requesting that the Second Circuit recall its mandate, vacate its"
"902","prior decision, and remand the actions to the District Court for further proceedings in light of the Supreme Court&rsquo;s decision"
"903","in <I>Merit Management</I>. The Second Circuit issued an order recalling the mandate &ldquo;in anticipation of further panel review&rdquo;"
"904","on May 16, 2018.</P>"
"905","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify>&nbsp;</P>"
"906","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.5in>The lawsuits allege no"
"907","misconduct by the Hussman Entities, and each of them intends to defend itself vigorously in the lawsuits. Although the outcome"
"908","of these proceedings cannot be predicted, the adverse impact to Hussman Strategic Growth Fund is not expected to exceed materially"
"909","the value of the proceeds received by the Fund in connection with the leveraged buyout, which was $29,432,814 (representing, as"
"910","of June 30, 2018, approximately 9.1% of the Fund&rsquo;s net assets), plus interest. If the proceedings are decided or settled"
"911","in a manner adverse to Hussman Strategic Growth Fund, the payment of judgments or settlements by the Fund in connection with the"
"912","proceedings could have a material adverse effect on its net asset value per share.</P>"
"913","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0>&nbsp;</P>"
